ENTRY            D6092   20260414   20260528   20260528       D152
SUBENT        D6092001   20260414   20260528   20260528       D152
BIB                 12         39
TITLE      A study of excitation functions for some residues
            produced in 16O+74Ge system below 7 MeV/nucleon
AUTHOR     (D.Singh, M.Afzal Ansari, R.Ali, N.P.M.Sathik,
           M.Ismail)
INSTITUTE  (3INDMUA,3INDVEC)
           (3INDIND) Jamal Mohammed College, Trichurapalli
REFERENCE  (J,CHP,46,27,200802)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,3INDVEC)
SAMPLE     (32-GE-74,ENR=0.989) The target of thickness
            80-270 ug/cm2 was prepared by vacuum evaporation onto
            Al foils (1.14 mg/cm2, 15 mm diameter)
DETECTOR   (HPGE) 100 cm3 detector of resolution 1.9 keV at
            1333 keV 60CO gamma-ray.
METHOD     (ACTIV,BCINT,STTA) The stack targets were irradiated
            for about 9 hours. The average beam current of about
            70 nA behind the target assembly was measured with
            electron suppressed Faraday cup. The beam fluences
            was measured to be 2300 uC in each irradiation.
COMMENT    Theoretical estimates of the cross-sections are
            obtained using statistical model based code PACE-2
            that uses the Monte-Carlo simulation technique
            for the de-excitation of a compound nucleus. The
            optical model parameters for the emitted particles
            (neutrons, protons, and alphas), and the average
            gamma transition strength are taken from the
            systematics.
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-T) Total uncertainty is due to:
           (ERR-1,,2.) The non-uniformity in the target material
             thickness (<2%)
           (ERR-2,,6.) Fluctuations in the beam current (<6%)
           (ERR-3,,5.) Detector efficiency (<5%)
           (ERR-4,,1.) Decrease in the oxygen ion beam intensity
                       (<1%)
           (ERR-5,,2.) Straggling of the ion beam (<2%)
STATUS     (APRVD) Entry approved by Dr.N.P.Sathik + NDS
           (TABLE,,D.Singh+,J,CHP,46,27,200802) Table II
HISTORY    (20091105C) compiled by author: Dr.N.P.Sathik
           (20260414A) VT. Revision in 007,010. BIB section
            updated.
ENDBIB              39
